Notes for Assignment 2:
1) command interpreter will have a prompt : $>
2) will be able to exit with "exit" or ctrl-d
3) unix redirection symbols may be used
4) must be able to run any program or unix command from the working directory of the CLI
5) must implement exit, cd, pwd (internal)
Listf
- must be in alphabetical order without attention to case
- if no directory specified, list current directory contents
- will be an external program which is run by a child of the CLI process
calc
- simple calculator takes single arithmetic operations from stdi and writes the formatted expression to stdout
- handles integers
- addition, subtraction mutliplication (*) and division (/)
- external program
- must be possible to run calc and listf regardless of current working directory
